<p><b>Learn by Reading:</b><br />
<img src="/img/excel-vba-book.png" style="width: 250px; height: auto; float: left; padding: 20px;" />
<img src="/img/finance-vba-book.png" style="width: 250px; height: auto; float: left; padding: 20px;" />
<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Excel-Power-Programming-Spreadsheets-Bookshelf/dp/1119067723">Excel 2016 Power Programming with VBA</a> is my favourite book for learning Excel VBA programming. This book provides a comprehensive overview of the programming language and enables learners to practise VBA with practical examples. You can buy on Amazon or find free copies from the Web. 
<br /><br />
Another book I highly recommend is <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Financial-Modeling-Using-Excel-Finance/dp/0471267686">Financial Modeling Using Excel and VBA</a> - another excellent resource for learning VBA. I think VBA is not hard to learn, but itâ€™s important to know why you want to learn VBA. If youâ€™re a financial engineer, you will find specialised learning resources like this more helpful than general VBA tutorials. Again, you can find free copies of this book on the Internet.
<br /><br /><br /><br />
In addition to these books, you can find good readings on tutoring websites such as:</p>
